scenario_text: Introduce a constraint that requires each vehicle to serve at least 5 distinct customer locations, assessing the impact on route optimization, feasibility, and total cost when enforcing minimum delivery stops per vehicle.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "for v in range(K): model += lpSum(x[i][j] for i in customers for j in nodes if j != i) >= 5, f'MinStops_Vehicle_{v}'"}

scenario_text: Increase the demand at the customer location with the highest initial demand by 300% to assess the impact on route feasibility and the need for additional logistics resources.

Introduce a constraint that requires all customers with a demand of 5 or more to be served in consecutive trips by the same vehicle, testing the impact on route feasibility, logistics synchronization, and overall cost.
code_modification: {"ADD CONSTRAINT": "for i in customers: model += lpSum(x[i][j] for j in customers if demand[i] >= 5) == lpSum(x[j][i] for j in customers if demand[i] >= 5), f'ConsecutiveTrips_{i}'"}
